WEBVTT

00:00:43.268 --> 00:00:45.479
There you go!

00:00:45.479 --> 00:00:47.350
Catch it.

00:00:48.023 --> 00:00:49.564
Gosh.

00:00:49.564 --> 00:00:52.235
It's sunny,
so why is it thundering so ominously?

00:00:52.235 --> 00:00:53.181
Dad,

00:00:53.181 --> 00:00:55.155
my mood was just right.

00:00:55.155 --> 00:00:55.907
Oh, my bad.

00:00:55.907 --> 00:00:58.226
Even thunder can't mess with your vibe.

00:00:58.226 --> 00:01:00.744
Never mind. I'm done shooting.

00:01:00.744 --> 00:01:01.772
What's wrong?

00:01:01.772 --> 00:01:03.651
Where are you going?

00:01:24.313 --> 00:01:26.436
Hi there.

00:01:26.436 --> 00:01:30.399
I'm Lee Ui Yeong. We spoke on the phone.

00:01:31.858 --> 00:01:33.771
Excuse me?

00:01:39.116 --> 00:01:41.373
Sir?

00:01:41.373 --> 00:01:42.994
Sir?

00:01:42.994 --> 00:01:45.914
- What?
- Gosh!

00:01:45.914 --> 00:01:47.541
I'm really sorry about that!

00:01:47.541 --> 00:01:49.418
So sorry!

00:01:50.877 --> 00:01:53.630
My apologies!

00:01:56.466 --> 00:01:58.522
Wait, Tae Seop?

00:01:58.522 --> 00:02:01.048
How come you're here?

00:02:03.181 --> 00:02:04.849
Did you

00:02:04.849 --> 00:02:06.293
come all this way for me?

00:02:06.293 --> 00:02:08.073
What? Me?

00:02:08.073 --> 00:02:10.891
Oh, not at all. It's a work thing.

00:02:11.647 --> 00:02:13.553
Hold on, are you...

00:02:13.553 --> 00:02:15.506
Lee Eun Ho?

00:02:15.506 --> 00:02:16.611
I'm the CEO of HOME.

00:02:16.611 --> 00:02:18.453
Oh, I thought...

00:02:18.453 --> 00:02:20.593
So you're the CEO of...

00:02:20.593 --> 00:02:22.393
What?

00:02:27.122 --> 00:02:29.963
Dad, some lady's over at Uncle's tent.

00:02:29.963 --> 00:02:32.871
What are you talking about?

00:02:35.630 --> 00:02:38.813
[Episode 4]

00:02:47.433 --> 00:02:49.346
Thank you.

00:03:03.700 --> 00:03:07.579
So you both run the company together?

00:03:11.355 --> 00:03:13.980
What's your name?

00:03:13.980 --> 00:03:15.823
- Lee Sua.
- I see.

00:03:15.823 --> 00:03:18.603
She's my daughter. She's seven.

00:03:18.603 --> 00:03:22.804
You had no clue he ran HOME?

00:03:22.804 --> 00:03:23.524
No.

00:03:23.524 --> 00:03:26.258
I heard you two were set up once.

00:03:27.432 --> 00:03:29.058
A buddy and I started

00:03:29.058 --> 00:03:32.186
a space branding firm called HOME.

00:03:32.186 --> 00:03:33.981
A space brand...

00:03:33.981 --> 00:03:37.441
Sounds like you two have a great bond.

00:03:37.441 --> 00:03:38.809
Yeah.

00:03:39.444 --> 00:03:40.737
- You were aware the whole time.
- Yeah.

00:03:40.737 --> 00:03:43.355
Wait, you knew?

00:03:43.355 --> 00:03:47.702
A quick call or message would've been nice.

00:03:47.702 --> 00:03:49.722
We could've avoided this whole mess.

00:03:49.722 --> 00:03:52.457
I thought the job would reveal it on its own.

00:03:52.457 --> 00:03:54.521
Yet look where we ended up.

00:03:54.521 --> 00:03:56.355
Right...

00:03:56.355 --> 00:03:57.629
We kind of brought this on ourselves.

00:03:57.629 --> 00:04:02.439
Who told you we were camping here?

00:04:02.439 --> 00:04:03.760
Were you tracking us down?

00:04:03.760 --> 00:04:06.021
Nothing shady.

00:04:06.021 --> 00:04:07.772
All above board.

00:04:07.772 --> 00:04:09.634
Thank you.

00:04:10.396 --> 00:04:12.143
Excuse me. Hello.

00:04:12.143 --> 00:04:14.882
Any idea where in Chuncheon I can find the CEO?

00:04:14.882 --> 00:04:15.422
Sorry?

00:04:15.422 --> 00:04:18.149
There's something I must tell him.

00:04:18.149 --> 00:04:21.146
He's going to wish he heard me out.

00:04:23.230 --> 00:04:24.780
What I

00:04:24.780 --> 00:04:27.146
wanted to say is...

00:04:27.146 --> 00:04:29.405
I'm truly sorry.

00:04:29.405 --> 00:04:30.855
I've learned

00:04:30.855 --> 00:04:34.123
that overstepping starts with thinking

00:04:34.123 --> 00:04:35.486
"this much is fine."

00:04:35.486 --> 00:04:38.063
I also owe you another apology

00:04:38.063 --> 00:04:40.588
for the copied designs.

00:04:40.588 --> 00:04:43.466
The news said

00:04:43.466 --> 00:04:44.826
the hotel was unaware too.

00:04:44.826 --> 00:04:46.511
You're right, we were in the dark.

00:04:46.511 --> 00:04:49.318
Still, better due diligence on our end

00:04:49.318 --> 00:04:53.271
could've prevented it.

00:04:53.271 --> 00:04:56.480
I can't believe you showed up
just because I said to.

00:04:56.480 --> 00:04:57.897
How are you this cooperative?

00:04:57.897 --> 00:05:00.566
Now I feel like the villain.

00:05:00.566 --> 00:05:01.067
Not at all.

00:05:01.067 --> 00:05:03.903
To be fair,
Tae Seop carried most of the weight.

00:05:03.903 --> 00:05:05.480
Around the clock, really.

00:05:05.480 --> 00:05:09.063
Anyway...

00:05:09.063 --> 00:05:10.396
apology accepted.

00:05:10.396 --> 00:05:11.726
Thank you so much.

00:05:11.726 --> 00:05:13.746
Seriously, I appreciate it.

00:05:13.746 --> 00:05:15.426
Okay, time to say something.

00:05:15.426 --> 00:05:17.859
Tell them about the fresh pitch.

00:05:17.859 --> 00:05:20.605
Explain how this deal works out for all of us.

00:05:20.605 --> 00:05:23.652
Show them they can't lose.

00:05:23.652 --> 00:05:26.503
Those words should be coming out, but...

00:05:27.677 --> 00:05:29.888
Come on, just say it...

00:05:31.521 --> 00:05:33.593
Just open your mouth...

00:05:34.184 --> 00:05:35.727
My lips won't move.

00:05:35.727 --> 00:05:38.730
Anything else on your mind?

00:05:38.730 --> 00:05:40.600
Actually...

00:05:43.104 --> 00:05:44.694
I came with presents.

00:05:44.694 --> 00:05:47.155
I brought a few things from the hotel.

00:05:47.155 --> 00:05:49.866
Well, this seat seems to be for me?

00:05:49.866 --> 00:05:50.909
Here's some meat.

00:05:50.909 --> 00:05:52.855
And Sua,

00:05:52.855 --> 00:05:55.079
I brought chocolate for you.

00:05:55.079 --> 00:05:56.879
Looks tasty, huh?

00:05:58.333 --> 00:05:59.396
Right.

00:05:59.396 --> 00:06:00.860
Bringing up business

00:06:00.860 --> 00:06:03.472
right after saying sorry is tacky.

00:06:03.472 --> 00:06:07.021
Let me ease the tension first,
get them comfortable.

00:06:07.021 --> 00:06:09.135
Looks like we can skip the grocery run.

00:06:09.135 --> 00:06:11.412
And after that, I'll make my move.

00:06:11.412 --> 00:06:14.634
Since you traveled so far, eat with us.

00:06:15.441 --> 00:06:17.762
Can I lend a hand at all?

00:06:17.762 --> 00:06:20.142
Oh, please relax.

00:06:20.142 --> 00:06:21.731
I'd never ask a guest to do chores.

00:06:21.731 --> 00:06:23.313
All right.

00:06:23.313 --> 00:06:27.147
So what are you going to do?

00:06:29.021 --> 00:06:31.234
You were waiting for her to reach out.

00:06:33.766 --> 00:06:37.042
Head down by the river and get some air.

00:06:37.042 --> 00:06:38.807
Let me take care of this.

00:06:46.407 --> 00:06:48.907
Everything's handled on this end.

00:06:48.907 --> 00:06:50.962
You've got this.

00:06:55.181 --> 00:06:56.887
Hyun Min.

00:06:56.887 --> 00:06:58.104
Yeah?

00:06:58.104 --> 00:07:01.807
Getting a permanent spot seems unlikely, huh?

00:07:01.807 --> 00:07:03.855
Well...

00:07:03.855 --> 00:07:07.687
Nobody can predict that yet.

00:07:07.687 --> 00:07:09.628
How about food and some soju?

00:07:09.628 --> 00:07:11.487
Not tonight. Let's do it another day.

00:07:11.487 --> 00:07:13.053
Sae Byeok,

00:07:13.053 --> 00:07:15.368
treat yourself this weekend.

00:07:15.368 --> 00:07:18.288
Find something entertaining to watch,
and stop worrying so much.

00:07:18.288 --> 00:07:21.868
The future's a mystery for everyone,

00:07:21.868 --> 00:07:22.917
right?

00:07:22.917 --> 00:07:25.163
- All right.
- Things will fall into place.

00:07:39.934 --> 00:07:41.183
Sua,

00:07:41.183 --> 00:07:42.395
I'll be your camerawoman.

00:07:42.395 --> 00:07:44.521
No thanks.

00:07:44.521 --> 00:07:45.924
You didn't even check.

00:07:45.924 --> 00:07:47.744
I'm so good.

00:07:47.744 --> 00:07:48.604
What vibe?

00:07:48.604 --> 00:07:50.424
Vertical? Face cam?

00:07:50.424 --> 00:07:53.730
Or like a performance video style?

00:07:53.730 --> 00:07:55.700
Okay, you know what you're doing.

00:07:55.700 --> 00:07:58.905
Make me look taller.

00:07:59.578 --> 00:08:02.874
If it comes out good,
you owe me some hangout time.

00:08:02.874 --> 00:08:05.301
- Okay.
- Okay.

00:08:07.503 --> 00:08:09.332
Make you look tall?

00:08:10.664 --> 00:08:13.146
Oh, you look so much taller.

00:08:13.146 --> 00:08:15.088
Not perfect yet.

00:08:15.730 --> 00:08:17.530
Give me a sec.

00:08:22.977 --> 00:08:24.777
Sua, come here real quick.

00:08:27.438 --> 00:08:29.564
Perfect! Have a look.

00:08:29.564 --> 00:08:31.569
So cute.

00:08:31.569 --> 00:08:33.238
Are you happy with it?

00:08:34.021 --> 00:08:36.985
So pretty. The weather makes it even better.

00:08:38.344 --> 00:08:40.245
Sua, turn this way and look here.

00:08:40.245 --> 00:08:41.955
That's it.

00:08:42.647 --> 00:08:44.447
Great.

00:08:45.980 --> 00:08:47.969
Sua, move to the flower side, right here.

00:08:47.969 --> 00:08:49.147
Perfect.

00:08:49.147 --> 00:08:50.989
Good, come closer.

00:08:50.989 --> 00:08:52.789
Yeah.

00:08:53.802 --> 00:08:54.809
Hold it right there.

00:08:54.809 --> 00:08:56.208
Perfect.

00:08:56.208 --> 00:08:57.308
Here, have a look.

00:08:57.308 --> 00:08:58.930
Check it out. What do you think?

00:08:58.930 --> 00:09:00.068
I love it.

00:09:00.068 --> 00:09:02.104
Nailed it, right?

00:09:02.104 --> 00:09:03.169
It's Uncle!

00:09:03.169 --> 00:09:05.055
Hey, Uncle!

00:09:20.659 --> 00:09:21.870
[Too bad, no new chats yet...]

00:09:21.870 --> 00:09:24.088
[28 people favorited me!]

00:09:27.021 --> 00:09:29.355
I look this attractive

00:09:29.355 --> 00:09:31.873
and not one date lined up.

00:09:34.355 --> 00:09:36.878
I don't want to swipe anymore.

00:09:38.973 --> 00:09:41.007
I'll just read comics.

00:09:45.730 --> 00:09:47.555
Soonmu.

00:09:53.028 --> 00:09:55.027
I'm interested in the comics you posted.

00:09:55.027 --> 00:09:58.230
They're not too outdated to read now, right?

00:09:58.230 --> 00:10:00.229
Alright, the time has come to send you off.

00:10:00.229 --> 00:10:04.408
I'll take good care so the value stays up.

00:10:04.408 --> 00:10:05.663
Outdated?

00:10:05.663 --> 00:10:06.789
These are classics.

00:10:06.789 --> 00:10:10.286
Timeless masterpieces.

00:10:12.587 --> 00:10:15.764
Are there plenty of attractive guys in it?

00:10:15.764 --> 00:10:16.799
For sure,

00:10:16.799 --> 00:10:19.087
the illustrations are unreal.

00:10:21.850 --> 00:10:23.050
Oh, nice.

00:10:23.050 --> 00:10:25.131
I can't wait to start reading.
Can we meet today?

00:10:25.131 --> 00:10:27.370
Let me see the condition first,
then I'll take it.

00:10:27.370 --> 00:10:28.561
Today?

00:10:28.561 --> 00:10:29.355
[Ready to move forward with this buyer?]

00:10:29.355 --> 00:10:32.267
[Reserved]
Bet she'll love this one.

00:10:34.608 --> 00:10:36.408
Okay.

00:10:39.280 --> 00:10:41.532
What's your go-to malatang order?

00:10:41.532 --> 00:10:43.931
Glass noodles and fried tofu for me.

00:10:43.931 --> 00:10:44.791
You?

00:10:44.791 --> 00:10:47.664
Snow fungus and dried tofu skin for me.

00:10:47.664 --> 00:10:48.371
Oh yeah?

00:10:48.371 --> 00:10:49.939
Hold on, Sua.

00:10:49.939 --> 00:10:52.919
Did you call her "unnie"?

00:10:52.919 --> 00:10:54.499
You never warm up to strangers this fast.

00:10:54.499 --> 00:10:56.332
That's not true!

00:10:57.939 --> 00:11:00.818
Tae Seop, are you getting dinner ready?

00:11:00.818 --> 00:11:02.418
That's right.

00:11:02.418 --> 00:11:04.257
Sua, here...

00:11:05.063 --> 00:11:07.010
Over here.

00:11:11.313 --> 00:11:13.349
I can carry it.

00:11:28.591 --> 00:11:32.243
How did he know my shoes were wet?

00:11:45.621 --> 00:11:49.151
That's my girl, Sua.

00:11:51.813 --> 00:11:54.071
This is super fresh!

00:11:54.071 --> 00:11:58.895
Look at Sua, all grown up now, huh?

00:12:11.247 --> 00:12:12.332
You alright?

00:12:12.332 --> 00:12:13.939
Gosh...

00:12:13.939 --> 00:12:16.329
- Hand it over. I got it.
- Yeah.

00:12:18.313 --> 00:12:21.438
Sorry, I just wanted to pitch in.

00:12:21.438 --> 00:12:24.411
I get it, but just go have a seat.

00:12:24.411 --> 00:12:25.612
You're too close to the flame. Not safe.

00:12:25.612 --> 00:12:28.731
Yeah, come here.

00:12:37.939 --> 00:12:39.772
Get me some juice, please.

00:12:39.772 --> 00:12:40.772
Do I look like your waiter?

00:12:40.772 --> 00:12:42.826
Thanks.

00:12:42.826 --> 00:12:44.781
One more, please.

00:12:44.781 --> 00:12:46.985
- Ask nicely.
- Please.

00:12:54.523 --> 00:12:57.954
Unnie, your face is super red right now.

00:12:58.647 --> 00:13:00.857
You look like a baked sweet potato.

00:13:00.857 --> 00:13:02.876
Oh, really?

00:13:07.303 --> 00:13:09.132
It's just so warm in here.

00:13:15.325 --> 00:13:17.682
Meat's ready.

00:13:19.148 --> 00:13:22.152
- Help yourselves.
- Thank you, I'll enjoy it.

00:13:22.985 --> 00:13:24.032
Good?

00:13:24.032 --> 00:13:26.149
We should scrap the interior design business.

00:13:27.980 --> 00:13:31.372
This is incredible. It's so tender.

00:13:31.372 --> 00:13:33.772
There's a ton of meat left.

00:13:33.772 --> 00:13:36.052
Just have some with us for now.

00:13:36.052 --> 00:13:38.104
Yeah, grab a bite too.

00:13:38.104 --> 00:13:39.173
Here, Sua, say "ah."

00:13:39.173 --> 00:13:40.553
I'm fine. I don't want any.

00:13:40.553 --> 00:13:42.132
My stomach's not empty.

00:13:42.132 --> 00:13:44.153
What? Don't come crying when it's all gone.

00:13:44.153 --> 00:13:45.956
I'm going to eat it all.

00:13:45.956 --> 00:13:48.110
- Huh?
- What?

00:13:52.563 --> 00:13:54.851
I think she'll want food later tonight.

00:13:54.851 --> 00:13:57.388
She snacked too much during the day.

00:13:58.897 --> 00:14:00.979
What animal does Sua like?

00:14:00.979 --> 00:14:02.879
A rabbit, a bear, or a swan?

00:14:02.879 --> 00:14:04.098
She loves them all, honestly.

00:14:04.098 --> 00:14:06.659
- Rabbits?
- Rabbits, huh?

00:15:05.588 --> 00:15:08.575
Suite guest Ms. Sua,

00:15:08.575 --> 00:15:09.995
your room service is here.

00:15:09.995 --> 00:15:14.298
Here are some mini burgers just for you.

00:15:26.442 --> 00:15:28.771
Enjoy your meal.

00:15:36.230 --> 00:15:38.611
Soonmu.

00:15:38.611 --> 00:15:39.692
I'm here.

00:15:39.692 --> 00:15:41.743
I'm in the red hoodie.

00:16:01.185 --> 00:16:02.772
You're JoongKkeokMa, right?

00:16:02.772 --> 00:16:04.563
Actually,

00:16:04.563 --> 00:16:05.792
it's JoongKkakMa,

00:16:05.792 --> 00:16:10.068
like "what matters is unshakable spirit."

00:16:10.068 --> 00:16:11.438
- What?
- Well...

00:16:11.438 --> 00:16:12.600
So you're HeungCheongMangCheong?

00:16:12.600 --> 00:16:14.688
My username is HeungJeongMangJeong.

00:16:14.688 --> 00:16:16.569
I see...

00:16:22.939 --> 00:16:27.480
If there's even a booger smudge on these,
the deal's off.

00:16:27.480 --> 00:16:29.813
I'm not that kind of person, okay?

00:16:29.813 --> 00:16:31.188
Oh, please.

00:16:31.188 --> 00:16:34.087
Everyone picks their nose.

00:16:38.389 --> 00:16:41.935
Hey, we're not at a manga cafe here.

00:16:43.063 --> 00:16:45.306
I zone in fast, that's all.

00:16:45.306 --> 00:16:47.327
Don't make it weird.

00:16:47.327 --> 00:16:48.565
So...

00:16:48.565 --> 00:16:52.146
skip these two worn ones
and knock off ten thousand won.

00:16:53.779 --> 00:16:56.157
No, this is a set. That doesn't work.

00:16:56.157 --> 00:16:59.763
Plus, this scene right here...

00:16:59.763 --> 00:17:03.986
You can't say you've read it
without seeing this part.

00:17:03.986 --> 00:17:06.047
Well, that's the reader's call.

00:17:06.047 --> 00:17:08.436
I'm buying this

00:17:08.436 --> 00:17:09.878
for this guy.

00:17:09.878 --> 00:17:12.917
I want to see this guy play basketball.

00:17:14.396 --> 00:17:16.197
Otherwise, at least cut me a deal.

00:17:16.197 --> 00:17:17.936
It says right in the listing.

00:17:17.936 --> 00:17:20.133
No haggling.

00:17:30.191 --> 00:17:32.855
My eyes hurt.

00:17:32.855 --> 00:17:35.154
All right then, how about we let a game decide?

00:17:35.154 --> 00:17:36.447
A game?

00:17:36.447 --> 00:17:37.615
So you don't actually plan to buy.

00:17:37.615 --> 00:17:39.533
- Hold on.
- You keep changing the subject...

00:17:39.533 --> 00:17:41.577
We're here over a basketball manga,
so why not play for it?

00:17:41.577 --> 00:17:44.271
I win, you drop ten thousand won.

00:17:44.271 --> 00:17:47.313
You win, I'll pay ten thousand more.

00:17:47.313 --> 00:17:49.113
Ten thousand won?

00:17:52.438 --> 00:17:56.240
You're challenging me to one-on-one?

00:17:56.240 --> 00:17:59.152
One on... what?

00:17:59.152 --> 00:18:02.098
No confidence in that?
Fine, we can rock-paper-scissors instead.

00:18:02.098 --> 00:18:04.643
Yeah, you're definitely scared.

00:18:07.271 --> 00:18:10.511
There's no way I lose in basketball.

00:18:10.511 --> 00:18:12.750
Okay, I'm ready.

00:18:12.750 --> 00:18:14.527
You sure you won't regret this?

00:18:14.527 --> 00:18:16.363
Deal.

00:18:18.772 --> 00:18:21.409
Hold on, this is an arcade game!

00:18:21.409 --> 00:18:22.647
What?

00:18:22.647 --> 00:18:24.230
Look at this.

00:18:24.230 --> 00:18:26.414
It's literally a basketball game.

00:18:26.414 --> 00:18:28.743
Any five-year-old could tell you.

00:18:30.021 --> 00:18:33.129
Fork over one thousand won to play.

00:18:33.129 --> 00:18:34.929
Come on, hurry.

00:18:38.396 --> 00:18:40.196
Okay.

00:18:42.346 --> 00:18:44.897
Let me show you how it's done.

00:18:44.897 --> 00:18:47.678
I'll go real easy on you.

00:19:11.375 --> 00:19:14.772
[Target Score, 20] [Your Score, 39]

00:19:14.772 --> 00:19:17.015
How is that all going in...

00:19:17.673 --> 00:19:19.091
[Time over]

00:19:19.091 --> 00:19:19.634
[Bonus points earned]

00:19:19.634 --> 00:19:21.897
Yes!

00:19:21.897 --> 00:19:25.230
You see that score? 145.

00:19:28.685 --> 00:19:30.311
Now you're up.

00:19:30.311 --> 00:19:32.356
Go ahead now.

00:19:37.902 --> 00:19:39.737
For someone who wasn't interested...

00:19:39.737 --> 00:19:40.655
Okay.

00:19:40.655 --> 00:19:42.953
My left hand only guides the ball.

00:19:47.980 --> 00:19:50.605
He's not bad.

00:19:50.605 --> 00:19:53.828
Seriously, knock it off!

00:19:54.438 --> 00:19:56.313
You're playing so dirty right now.

00:19:56.313 --> 00:19:57.688
What's dirty about it?

00:19:57.688 --> 00:20:00.835
I never said blocking was a foul.

00:20:01.759 --> 00:20:02.890
Okay.

00:20:02.890 --> 00:20:05.345
Then body contact's fair game too, right?

00:20:05.345 --> 00:20:07.145
[Three points]

00:20:08.015 --> 00:20:10.727
I need to focus.

00:20:27.201 --> 00:20:29.344
[GRADE, C, ACCURACY, 65%]
[TOTAL SCORE, 129]

00:20:32.915 --> 00:20:35.355
All right, let's make it best of three.

00:20:35.355 --> 00:20:36.710
Let's play a different game.

00:20:36.710 --> 00:20:39.647
What else is there?

00:20:39.647 --> 00:20:40.797
Bring it on.

00:20:40.797 --> 00:20:42.980
Get over here.

00:20:42.980 --> 00:20:45.218
Stop getting in my way like that.

00:20:45.218 --> 00:20:48.272
What? Look, right over there!

00:20:55.062 --> 00:20:57.065
You're finished!

00:21:03.855 --> 00:21:05.871
Okay.

00:21:09.104 --> 00:21:11.002
Drift.

00:21:12.288 --> 00:21:14.338
Come on.

00:21:16.625 --> 00:21:18.627
Did you catch my ultimate technique?

00:21:18.627 --> 00:21:21.757
- Don't talk to me informally.
- Okay.

00:21:33.017 --> 00:21:35.355
We are merely small specks

00:21:35.355 --> 00:21:38.988
in this infinite cosmos.

00:21:42.859 --> 00:21:43.897
Sua,

00:21:43.897 --> 00:21:46.894
I'm going to let you have a marshmallow today.

00:21:46.894 --> 00:21:48.605
- For real?
- Let's go.

00:21:48.605 --> 00:21:50.207
Let's go.

00:22:06.938 --> 00:22:09.230
- Do you feel uncomfortable?
- What?

00:22:09.230 --> 00:22:12.229
No, it is not awkward.

00:22:14.188 --> 00:22:16.099
- Did you see the shooting star?
- What?

00:22:16.099 --> 00:22:17.438
Hurry up and make a wish.

00:22:17.438 --> 00:22:19.563
I hope my mom, Seung Jun, Dad,

00:22:19.563 --> 00:22:22.439
Sua, Tae Seop, Eun Ho, and I
are all healthy and happy,

00:22:22.439 --> 00:22:23.900
and please let my salary increase,

00:22:23.900 --> 00:22:26.862
and since I've not given up on dating,
please look after me.

00:22:26.862 --> 00:22:30.074
Why do you have such a lengthy wish?

00:22:30.074 --> 00:22:33.577
I don't often get the opportunity
to make a wish.

00:22:33.577 --> 00:22:36.629
Did you wish for anything?

00:22:38.271 --> 00:22:40.123
Well, didn't you wish to get married?

00:22:40.123 --> 00:22:41.980
What?

00:22:41.980 --> 00:22:43.355
No. Why...

00:22:43.355 --> 00:22:45.942
You brought that up

00:22:45.942 --> 00:22:47.902
at our first meeting,

00:22:47.902 --> 00:22:50.518
and I was quite shocked.

00:22:51.402 --> 00:22:53.063
I'm...

00:22:53.063 --> 00:22:56.230
at an age for serious dating,

00:22:56.230 --> 00:22:57.396
and...

00:22:57.396 --> 00:23:01.779
I spoke too forcefully
while trying to say I'm interested in you.

00:23:05.652 --> 00:23:08.380
So that's what you meant?

00:23:08.380 --> 00:23:10.021
So,

00:23:10.021 --> 00:23:12.100
did you go on another date

00:23:12.100 --> 00:23:14.701
because I caught you off guard about marriage?

00:23:14.701 --> 00:23:16.855
Well, it did catch me by surprise.

00:23:16.855 --> 00:23:20.457
But you told me to go for it so coolly,

00:23:20.457 --> 00:23:24.301
so I figured you just weren't into me.

00:23:25.480 --> 00:23:28.055
I did, didn't I?

00:23:29.634 --> 00:23:31.660
It's strange, isn't it?

00:23:31.660 --> 00:23:36.272
Being considerate only drove us further apart.

00:23:37.084 --> 00:23:39.734
The more I try to ignore you,

00:23:40.688 --> 00:23:42.838
the more I can't help but notice you.

00:23:45.063 --> 00:23:48.355
I tried to keep it professional today, but...

00:23:48.355 --> 00:23:49.994
honestly,

00:23:52.263 --> 00:23:55.541
you're still all I can think about.

00:24:10.842 --> 00:24:13.396
Look, this is really good.

00:24:13.396 --> 00:24:15.011
Oh, thanks.

00:24:15.011 --> 00:24:16.882
Okay.

00:24:16.882 --> 00:24:18.181
Here.

00:24:18.181 --> 00:24:20.025
Give it to me.

00:24:29.903 --> 00:24:32.188
I know what he means

00:24:32.188 --> 00:24:35.658
about noticing someone

00:24:35.658 --> 00:24:37.792
the harder he tries to stop.

00:24:55.519 --> 00:24:58.647
Even though I've messed everything up,

00:24:58.647 --> 00:25:01.148
I find myself getting my hopes up again.

00:25:12.110 --> 00:25:14.197
Sua fell asleep.

00:25:18.104 --> 00:25:19.688
Oh, watch your step.

00:25:19.688 --> 00:25:21.877
I forgot about this one.

00:25:23.211 --> 00:25:26.551
I'll wash this quickly. Put Sua to bed.

00:25:26.551 --> 00:25:29.844
I'd appreciate that. Thanks.

00:25:42.433 --> 00:25:44.231
Hey.

00:25:44.231 --> 00:25:46.770
If she is okay with it,
let's ask her to sleep over.

00:25:46.770 --> 00:25:48.521
You and I can share a tent,

00:25:48.521 --> 00:25:51.021
and she can sleep with Sua.

00:25:51.021 --> 00:25:54.410
It's way too dark out here in the mountains.

00:25:55.772 --> 00:25:58.497
Yeah, I gotta tidy up the tent.

00:26:16.341 --> 00:26:18.684
[Dad, Uncle]

00:26:22.056 --> 00:26:25.208
[Whiskey Brand Pop-up Proposal]

00:26:35.693 --> 00:26:37.698
[Team Manager Oh Myeong Un]

00:26:37.698 --> 00:26:40.019
I totally forgot.

00:26:40.019 --> 00:26:42.750
Or was I just avoiding it?

00:26:45.438 --> 00:26:46.879
It's me.

00:26:46.879 --> 00:26:48.679
Did he agree to work with us?

00:26:48.679 --> 00:26:52.146
Well, I'm keeping an eye on things.

00:26:52.146 --> 00:26:55.396
I think we should wait until we're in Seoul

00:26:55.396 --> 00:26:57.336
to officially sit down

00:26:57.336 --> 00:26:59.217
and pitch the proposal...

00:26:59.217 --> 00:27:02.879
I mean, who takes a cab all the way
out to Chuncheon just to apologize?

00:27:02.879 --> 00:27:05.934
Since you're already there,
act like you own the place.

00:27:05.934 --> 00:27:07.772
Don't look pathetic, okay?

00:27:07.772 --> 00:27:08.479
Pathetic?

00:27:08.479 --> 00:27:12.918
If they say no, we just walk away. Simple.

00:27:12.918 --> 00:27:13.839
Got it?

00:27:13.839 --> 00:27:15.718
Hello?

00:27:15.718 --> 00:27:17.403
Is the signal bad?

00:27:17.403 --> 00:27:20.871
No, I hear you loud and clear.

00:27:22.188 --> 00:27:24.498
I'll talk to him.

00:27:24.498 --> 00:27:27.461
That's why I'm staying up so late for this.

00:27:31.073 --> 00:27:32.747
Okay.

00:27:41.772 --> 00:27:43.273
Nina,

00:27:43.273 --> 00:27:45.807
I cursed and resented you.

00:27:45.807 --> 00:27:48.933
I tore up your letters and photographs.

00:27:48.933 --> 00:27:51.063
But I never forgot

00:27:51.063 --> 00:27:53.454
that my soul is tied

00:27:53.454 --> 00:27:55.948
to yours for eternity.

00:27:59.433 --> 00:28:02.413
I can't bring myself to hate you, Nina.

00:28:09.521 --> 00:28:10.957
Great work out there today.

00:28:10.957 --> 00:28:12.134
You all did great.

00:28:12.134 --> 00:28:13.289
Great job, everyone.

00:28:13.289 --> 00:28:16.343
- Let's wrap up and go grab a drink.
- Sounds good.

00:28:24.295 --> 00:28:25.303
For the wrap party.

00:28:25.303 --> 00:28:28.306
Yeah, our usual BBQ spot by the park.

00:28:28.306 --> 00:28:31.121
Actually, want to make it just us two?

00:28:31.121 --> 00:28:34.737
I'd love to get to know you better.

00:28:42.021 --> 00:28:46.574
If you ignore how people feel...
Do you think you can be a good actor?

00:28:46.574 --> 00:28:49.533
Hey, Eun A is quitting after tonight.

00:28:49.533 --> 00:28:50.262
Just letting you all know.

00:28:50.262 --> 00:28:53.440
A new hire finally joined and is leaving?

00:28:53.440 --> 00:28:55.040
It's obvious.

00:28:55.040 --> 00:28:57.001
Boy-girl drama.

00:28:57.001 --> 00:28:59.671
She hung out with Shin Ji Su for a while.

00:28:59.671 --> 00:29:03.341
I mean, he's not even acting.
He's actually trying to seduce people.

00:29:03.341 --> 00:29:07.200
Actors, the audience, everyone.

00:29:07.200 --> 00:29:09.321
She's my scene partner.
I was just looking out for her.

00:29:09.321 --> 00:29:10.520
You hear that?

00:29:10.520 --> 00:29:12.563
Sounds like a compliment, not a diss.

00:29:12.563 --> 00:29:14.018
Look, my point is...

00:29:14.018 --> 00:29:16.152
Seriously though, stop stirring things up here

00:29:16.152 --> 00:29:17.960
and just go do movies or dramas.

00:29:17.960 --> 00:29:18.421
For real.

00:29:18.421 --> 00:29:21.819
You've got directors lining up to cast you.

00:29:21.819 --> 00:29:22.989
Drop it.

00:29:22.989 --> 00:29:25.746
Life's exhausting enough as it is.

00:29:28.992 --> 00:29:30.480
You guys killed the vibe.

00:29:30.480 --> 00:29:31.550
I'm leaving.

00:29:31.550 --> 00:29:33.980
Hey, if you leave,
who's going to grill the meat?

00:29:33.980 --> 00:29:35.189
You hungry?

00:29:35.189 --> 00:29:38.584
You guys have been roasting me
so hard I figured you were full.

00:29:38.584 --> 00:29:40.649
- Where should I...
- I'll take that.

00:29:41.647 --> 00:29:43.693
Grill your own damn meat, all right?

00:29:44.770 --> 00:29:46.729
And don't come looking for me.

00:29:46.729 --> 00:29:48.489
You have nowhere else to go.

00:29:48.489 --> 00:29:49.610
The theater's basically your home.

00:29:49.610 --> 00:29:51.237
You're seriously leaving?

00:29:51.237 --> 00:29:53.857
Didn't you just get fired
from your part-time job?

00:30:31.763 --> 00:30:33.682
You've been standing here a while.

00:30:33.682 --> 00:30:35.985
Is there anything I can help you with?

00:30:35.985 --> 00:30:38.805
No, I'm good.

00:30:38.805 --> 00:30:40.904
Here, take this.

00:30:42.772 --> 00:30:45.117
It smells really nice.

00:30:46.104 --> 00:30:47.870
Take care.

00:31:01.668 --> 00:31:02.918
[airy] [Part-time help wanted]

00:31:02.918 --> 00:31:05.143
[Duties,
Drinks, customer service, cleaning, etc.]

00:31:09.844 --> 00:31:13.387
So there's this movie
Director Jin's working on in secret.

00:31:13.387 --> 00:31:15.097
[Dokgo]
The female lead is a gardener

00:31:15.097 --> 00:31:16.390
who's slowly losing her sight.

00:31:16.390 --> 00:31:19.313
She's waiting for an old love
who may never come back,

00:31:19.313 --> 00:31:22.788
tending a garden full of poisonous plants.

00:31:23.815 --> 00:31:26.069
It's a thriller-romance.

00:31:26.069 --> 00:31:27.855
So?

00:31:27.855 --> 00:31:30.556
Is Director Jin going to cast me?

00:31:30.556 --> 00:31:32.257
I heard my scandal's got him on the fence.

00:31:32.257 --> 00:31:33.497
Oh, come on.

00:31:33.497 --> 00:31:35.256
Since when do tabloid rumors matter?

00:31:35.256 --> 00:31:36.996
Nothing official even came out.

00:31:36.996 --> 00:31:38.497
We've got a meeting set up.

00:31:38.497 --> 00:31:40.373
So just relax at a hotel for a few days,

00:31:40.373 --> 00:31:42.816
recharge, and then we'll reconnect.

00:31:42.816 --> 00:31:45.552
We've got to get back to Cannes.

00:31:49.215 --> 00:31:51.391
Pull over for a sec.

00:31:53.479 --> 00:31:55.187
Ji Su!

00:31:57.271 --> 00:31:59.320
You got even more handsome
since I last saw you.

00:31:59.320 --> 00:32:01.039
Why aren't you picking up my calls?

00:32:01.039 --> 00:32:03.737
Aren't we close enough to talk on the phone?

00:32:04.559 --> 00:32:06.615
Need some spending money?

00:32:09.455 --> 00:32:10.480
What?

00:32:10.480 --> 00:32:13.600
An adult is talking.
Who does he take after with that attitude...

00:32:13.600 --> 00:32:16.459
Want to pop in for a bit?

00:32:16.459 --> 00:32:18.179
Forget it.

00:32:18.179 --> 00:32:20.504
He can't avoid me forever.

00:32:21.416 --> 00:32:23.674
I'm tired. Let's go.

00:32:26.875 --> 00:32:30.055
So you're just sending her away?

00:32:35.605 --> 00:32:37.354
Look, Ui Yeong...

00:32:39.313 --> 00:32:40.496
Well...

00:32:40.496 --> 00:32:44.815
it's getting really late
and the last train's about to stop running.

00:32:44.815 --> 00:32:47.456
Hey, can you give her a ride to the station?

00:32:47.456 --> 00:32:49.695
I can't drive. I had a beer.

00:32:49.695 --> 00:32:51.277
What?

00:32:53.813 --> 00:32:57.469
Tae Seop, why are you suddenly...

00:32:57.469 --> 00:33:00.089
Why did you come here?

00:33:00.089 --> 00:33:01.623
Sorry?

00:33:01.623 --> 00:33:05.882
Why did you stick around,
hanging out with us, being so nice?

00:33:08.146 --> 00:33:10.012
Oh, well, I...

00:33:13.730 --> 00:33:16.349
You didn't come here to apologize.

00:33:16.349 --> 00:33:18.149
Just say it.

00:33:18.149 --> 00:33:20.480
I'll hear you out. One last time.

00:33:22.605 --> 00:33:24.401
Well, the thing is...

00:33:25.246 --> 00:33:29.906
I was going to start with an apology,

00:33:30.971 --> 00:33:33.952
and then, this proposal...

00:33:35.230 --> 00:33:37.021
I reworked it

00:33:37.021 --> 00:33:40.468
in a way that benefits both sides.

00:33:40.468 --> 00:33:41.619
I mean, obviously,

00:33:41.619 --> 00:33:45.623
you already have a solid customer base,

00:33:45.623 --> 00:33:49.672
but if you partner with our hotel,

00:33:49.672 --> 00:33:52.048
it could really help

00:33:52.048 --> 00:33:55.932
get the brand out there...

00:33:57.134 --> 00:33:58.730
Are you done?

00:33:58.730 --> 00:34:00.687
Want me to call you a cab?

00:34:03.266 --> 00:34:04.983
No.

00:34:06.605 --> 00:34:09.112
I'll go on my own.

00:34:10.939 --> 00:34:13.200
Sorry for the trouble.

00:34:50.271 --> 00:34:52.813
How are you so good at every game?

00:34:52.813 --> 00:34:54.364
Did you just eat and play games all day?

00:34:54.364 --> 00:34:56.905
I'm good at winning.

00:34:56.905 --> 00:34:58.443
I'm in a good mood.

00:34:58.443 --> 00:35:01.343
I made some cash, so here's a free tip.

00:35:01.343 --> 00:35:04.095
I'm the one who made the money here.

00:35:04.095 --> 00:35:05.096
What's the tip?

00:35:05.096 --> 00:35:07.622
If you only play it straight like you do,

00:35:07.622 --> 00:35:09.596
you'll never beat someone like me.

00:35:09.596 --> 00:35:11.296
When you meet your match, just run. Okay?

00:35:11.296 --> 00:35:14.761
What kind of tip is that?

00:35:17.271 --> 00:35:20.934
Anyway, let's never see each other again.

00:35:21.678 --> 00:35:23.765
Wait...

00:35:25.975 --> 00:35:27.018
You...

00:35:27.018 --> 00:35:28.851
seem a bit bummed.

00:35:28.851 --> 00:35:31.194
How about one more deal with me?

00:35:32.293 --> 00:35:33.312
What kind of...

00:35:33.312 --> 00:35:35.313
This thing is so heavy.

00:35:35.313 --> 00:35:38.092
Carry it to my place
and I'll give you ten thousand won.

00:35:38.092 --> 00:35:40.287
Think of it as a delivery fee.

00:35:59.355 --> 00:36:03.219
Yeah, this is pretty heavy, actually.

00:36:03.219 --> 00:36:05.682
You better keep that promise.

00:36:11.563 --> 00:36:13.445
Yeah. Here.

00:36:22.188 --> 00:36:24.289
You knew I was hitting on you, right?

00:36:24.289 --> 00:36:26.897
You were being so obvious about it,

00:36:26.897 --> 00:36:28.746
I kind of had a feeling.

00:36:28.746 --> 00:36:30.242
And

00:36:30.242 --> 00:36:34.132
you still didn't run and came right along?

00:37:34.271 --> 00:37:36.194
Are you done?

00:37:36.941 --> 00:37:38.446
Done.

00:38:36.372 --> 00:38:39.090
[23:30 (Last Bus)]

00:38:40.791 --> 00:38:42.311
What?

00:38:42.311 --> 00:38:44.888
That was the last bus?

00:39:11.563 --> 00:39:14.918
Seriously, nothing is going my way today.

00:39:22.585 --> 00:39:24.631
Gosh.

00:39:26.214 --> 00:39:27.590
Sua, turn this way and look here.

00:39:27.590 --> 00:39:28.507
It's uncle!

00:39:28.507 --> 00:39:30.266
Uncle!

00:39:31.386 --> 00:39:33.054
- Did you see the shooting star?
- What?

00:39:33.054 --> 00:39:35.517
Hurry up and make a wish.

00:39:37.647 --> 00:39:39.859
Sorry for the trouble.

00:39:53.741 --> 00:39:55.828
[Ui Yeong]

00:39:55.828 --> 00:39:57.834
The person you are trying to reach
is unavailable.

00:39:57.834 --> 00:40:01.139
Please leave a message after the beep.

00:40:01.139 --> 00:40:03.238
Tae Seop!

00:40:03.238 --> 00:40:04.634
Song Tae Seop!

00:40:06.379 --> 00:40:07.972
It's pouring out here!

00:40:07.972 --> 00:40:09.739
It's like the sky split open!

00:40:09.739 --> 00:40:10.919
Oh crap, this is bad.

00:40:10.919 --> 00:40:12.259
We need to go, now.

00:40:12.259 --> 00:40:14.439
This tent can barely handle a drizzle.

00:40:14.439 --> 00:40:17.719
Pack everything up
and get to town with Sua ahead of me.

00:40:17.719 --> 00:40:18.619
What about you?

00:40:18.619 --> 00:40:20.438
I can't reach Ui Yeong.

00:40:20.438 --> 00:40:22.772
I need to make sure she got home safe.

00:40:22.772 --> 00:40:25.605
She's not answering.
How are you going to check?

00:40:25.605 --> 00:40:26.396
- I don't know.
- What?

00:40:26.396 --> 00:40:28.118
- I'll call you later.
- Hey.

00:40:28.118 --> 00:40:30.018
Song Tae Seop!

00:40:30.018 --> 00:40:31.661
Hey!

00:40:44.833 --> 00:40:46.968
It's so cold.

00:40:56.137 --> 00:40:58.809
I guess karma's finally catching up to me.

00:41:01.688 --> 00:41:04.188
Ui Yeong!

00:41:04.188 --> 00:41:06.524
Ui Yeong!

00:41:06.524 --> 00:41:08.169
Ui Yeong!

00:41:08.169 --> 00:41:10.526
Ui Yeong!

00:41:10.526 --> 00:41:11.530
Ui Yeong...

00:41:28.878 --> 00:41:29.906
You alright?

00:41:29.906 --> 00:41:30.896
I'm fine.

00:41:30.896 --> 00:41:35.216
By any chance, did a woman
come by here, about yea tall?

00:41:35.216 --> 00:41:36.177
Haven't seen anybody.

00:41:36.177 --> 00:41:37.256
Alright, thanks.

00:41:37.256 --> 00:41:38.816
Wait.

00:41:38.816 --> 00:41:40.797
Who could you possibly be chasing at this hour?

00:41:40.797 --> 00:41:42.599
The buses stopped running,

00:41:42.599 --> 00:41:44.617
and nothing but critters out here after dark.

00:41:44.617 --> 00:41:46.516
- Critters?
- That's right.

00:41:46.516 --> 00:41:49.257
Sir, any chance I could use this bike?

00:41:49.257 --> 00:41:51.457
I'll just loop around the area
and have it back to you.

00:41:51.457 --> 00:41:52.937
You're riding in this storm?

00:41:52.937 --> 00:41:54.696
Yes.

00:41:55.681 --> 00:41:56.842
Alright, go ahead.

00:41:56.842 --> 00:41:58.541
I appreciate it.

00:41:58.541 --> 00:42:02.126
- My place is just down over there...
- Yes, thank you so much.

00:42:05.748 --> 00:42:07.293
Ui Yeong!

00:42:07.293 --> 00:42:09.425
Ui Yeong!

00:42:14.396 --> 00:42:16.511
Ui Yeong!

00:42:16.511 --> 00:42:18.685
Ui Yeong!

00:43:03.455 --> 00:43:05.315
Ui Yeong.

00:43:07.897 --> 00:43:09.569
What?

00:43:25.038 --> 00:43:26.961
You alright?

00:43:27.772 --> 00:43:30.210
I'm okay, but...

00:43:30.210 --> 00:43:32.104
You came

00:43:32.104 --> 00:43:34.969
all the way through that downpour?

00:43:36.341 --> 00:43:38.640
You're completely drenched.

00:43:48.167 --> 00:43:50.944
Who are you really?

00:43:53.396 --> 00:43:54.901
Excuse me?

00:43:54.901 --> 00:43:57.647
How do you

00:43:57.647 --> 00:44:00.453
want me to remember you?

00:44:02.294 --> 00:44:07.460
We never could get our timing right.
It was always one step off.

00:44:11.855 --> 00:44:14.842
Everything you saw...

00:44:15.605 --> 00:44:18.554
I can't pretend that wasn't me.

00:44:21.647 --> 00:44:23.844
The only thing I know how to do now is

00:44:23.844 --> 00:44:26.847
lay it all out on the table.

00:44:26.847 --> 00:44:28.438
But

00:44:28.438 --> 00:44:31.651
there's more to me than that.

00:44:32.508 --> 00:44:36.280
I want you to see the rest.

00:44:38.563 --> 00:44:40.655
Give me

00:44:40.655 --> 00:44:43.621
a little time.

00:45:32.790 --> 00:45:35.271
Tae Seop,

00:45:35.271 --> 00:45:39.093
thank you for coming to find me.

00:45:40.688 --> 00:45:43.772
I'll show you I was worth it.

00:45:43.772 --> 00:45:45.207
Oh, stop,

00:45:45.207 --> 00:45:48.686
you sound like some politician
in a press conference.

00:45:49.647 --> 00:45:51.772
Besides...

00:45:51.772 --> 00:45:54.525
it wasn't all that terrible.

00:45:59.772 --> 00:46:03.659
Well, at least the rain stopped.

00:46:24.169 --> 00:46:25.569
How did we end up here again?

00:46:25.569 --> 00:46:26.829
I know I checked the map.

00:46:26.829 --> 00:46:28.349
Look, let's just get inside first.

00:46:28.349 --> 00:46:30.512
We're asking for trouble out here.

00:46:30.512 --> 00:46:32.063
Wait a second.

00:46:32.063 --> 00:46:34.899
Are you religious at all?

00:46:36.104 --> 00:46:40.355
If it helps, I'll start believing today.

00:46:40.355 --> 00:46:42.198
Amen.

00:47:01.017 --> 00:47:04.617
Dear Heavenly Father, sir,

00:47:04.617 --> 00:47:08.850
was this all part of your plan?

00:47:14.188 --> 00:47:18.097
We just need a roof for tonight.

00:47:18.097 --> 00:47:20.940
We won't make a peep, I promise.

00:47:20.940 --> 00:47:22.620
Amen.

00:47:23.355 --> 00:47:25.241
Ui Yeong.

00:47:32.776 --> 00:47:34.667
Thank you.

00:47:46.838 --> 00:47:48.215
I'm not even religious.

00:47:48.215 --> 00:47:52.597
I won't get struck down for sneaking in, right?

00:47:54.516 --> 00:47:56.731
Probably not.

00:47:57.432 --> 00:48:01.523
Still, we should slip out at first light
before people start coming in.

00:48:01.523 --> 00:48:03.345
Okay.

00:48:07.039 --> 00:48:08.512
Are you cold?

00:48:08.512 --> 00:48:09.732
No.

00:48:09.732 --> 00:48:12.659
It is much warmer than I was out there.

00:48:12.659 --> 00:48:15.332
It must be all that hair.

00:48:15.332 --> 00:48:17.521
It still looks completely soaked.

00:48:17.521 --> 00:48:19.079
Hey,

00:48:19.079 --> 00:48:21.964
face the other way for a moment?

00:48:22.877 --> 00:48:24.672
It'll dry on its own.

00:48:24.672 --> 00:48:26.086
That'll take forever.

00:48:26.086 --> 00:48:27.762
One second.

00:49:05.369 --> 00:49:06.939
I'm sorry.

00:49:06.939 --> 00:49:08.688
No, it's just...

00:49:08.688 --> 00:49:10.846
your hands are so warm.

00:49:56.521 --> 00:49:59.020
Should I really be doing this?

00:50:10.232 --> 00:50:11.775
If it's a sin,

00:50:11.775 --> 00:50:15.991
I'll pay for it someday.

00:50:46.685 --> 00:50:48.716
You're on bell duty later, right?

00:50:48.716 --> 00:50:49.776
Yeah.

00:50:49.776 --> 00:50:51.980
When's your turn?

00:50:51.980 --> 00:50:53.611
I go after you.

00:50:53.611 --> 00:50:55.409
Got it.

00:50:59.063 --> 00:51:01.499
Go bring Father over.

00:51:07.897 --> 00:51:10.128
They're definitely not here for the service.

00:51:10.128 --> 00:51:13.052
Look. They came here to sleep.

00:51:19.304 --> 00:51:22.353
She just opened her eyes.

00:51:26.271 --> 00:51:29.105
I'm so sorry.

00:51:29.105 --> 00:51:30.979
Tae Seop, wake up.

00:51:37.861 --> 00:51:41.705
You're the priest here?

00:51:42.772 --> 00:51:44.326
Hello.

00:51:44.326 --> 00:51:47.224
You actually came!

00:51:47.224 --> 00:51:48.533
Welcome.

00:51:48.533 --> 00:51:51.799
You know our priest?

00:52:05.438 --> 00:52:06.684
He's good-looking.

00:52:06.684 --> 00:52:07.933
Maybe I should've just left.

00:52:07.933 --> 00:52:09.939
Excuse me.

00:52:09.939 --> 00:52:13.381
Guests of the church are also guests of God.

00:52:13.381 --> 00:52:16.066
I cannot send you off hungry.

00:52:16.066 --> 00:52:17.867
Thank you.

00:52:25.396 --> 00:52:27.355
This is quite excellent.

00:52:27.355 --> 00:52:30.580
Nuns collected strawberries
from the hills and made jam.

00:52:30.580 --> 00:52:35.461
I roasted the beans slowly on a cast-iron lid.

00:52:35.461 --> 00:52:38.923
Oh, no wonder.
The coffee is incredibly rich and smooth.

00:52:38.923 --> 00:52:39.964
That hits the spot, doesn't it?

00:52:39.964 --> 00:52:40.803
Yes.

00:52:40.803 --> 00:52:44.435
If you enjoy it, consider attending church.

00:52:46.647 --> 00:52:50.122
Last night, I gained some trust.

00:52:50.122 --> 00:52:51.463
Did you sleep well?

00:52:51.463 --> 00:52:53.802
Using wooden chairs might be
uncomfortable for the back.

00:52:53.802 --> 00:52:55.021
No, everything was fine.

00:52:55.021 --> 00:52:57.193
We would've been in real trouble
if it weren't for this place.

00:52:57.193 --> 00:52:59.081
Thank you very much.

00:52:59.081 --> 00:53:01.897
The doors are always open here.

00:53:01.897 --> 00:53:03.697
But...

00:53:03.697 --> 00:53:05.301
What are you two, exactly?

00:53:05.301 --> 00:53:08.521
This calm one appears to take good care of you.

00:53:08.521 --> 00:53:10.741
Are you the boyfriend?

00:53:10.741 --> 00:53:13.301
Oh no, it's not like that.

00:53:13.301 --> 00:53:15.781
Just an acquaintance.

00:53:15.781 --> 00:53:17.593
Acquaintance?

00:53:26.772 --> 00:53:30.305
Not even friends or coworkers...

00:53:30.305 --> 00:53:33.768
I mean, technically,
"acquaintances" is correct.

00:53:33.768 --> 00:53:35.834
But we did kiss.

00:53:35.834 --> 00:53:37.905
And there was a witness.

00:53:43.063 --> 00:53:45.291
Eun Ho and Sua stayed overnight
at a place downtown

00:53:45.291 --> 00:53:46.993
and just checked out.

00:53:46.993 --> 00:53:51.148
You could ride back with us too.

00:53:51.148 --> 00:53:52.187
Oh, no, I'm fine.

00:53:52.187 --> 00:53:54.880
I'll just take the train.

00:53:55.480 --> 00:53:58.187
There would be too much to explain,

00:53:58.187 --> 00:54:00.754
like how we met

00:54:00.754 --> 00:54:03.419
and where we stayed.

00:54:03.419 --> 00:54:06.433
Oh, right, that's true.

00:54:25.943 --> 00:54:28.104
Well...

00:54:28.104 --> 00:54:29.999
yesterday...

00:54:35.497 --> 00:54:36.521
Yeah?

00:54:36.521 --> 00:54:38.424
Yesterday...

00:54:39.313 --> 00:54:41.034
Well...

00:54:43.730 --> 00:54:47.474
You can return the clothes
I lent you next time.

00:54:51.480 --> 00:54:53.105
Sure.

00:54:54.057 --> 00:54:57.730
I'll make sure to have them dry-cleaned

00:54:57.730 --> 00:55:00.154
and give them back to you.

00:55:40.497 --> 00:55:42.654
Number 26...

00:55:43.480 --> 00:55:45.407
Yeah, here it is.

00:56:53.853 --> 00:56:56.355
What are you doing here?

00:56:56.355 --> 00:56:58.396
It's my first time riding without a ticket.

00:56:58.396 --> 00:57:01.775
If they catch me,
think I'd owe like, ten times the price?

00:57:15.063 --> 00:57:18.193
The rain's being so wishy-washy.

00:57:18.193 --> 00:57:21.747
But I bet it'll clear up pretty soon.

00:57:21.747 --> 00:57:23.286
What about Uncle?

00:57:23.286 --> 00:57:25.845
Looks like he tracked her down.

00:57:25.845 --> 00:57:28.188
They managed to find each other this time.

00:57:28.188 --> 00:57:30.286
Wait, weren't they fighting?

00:57:30.286 --> 00:57:33.688
A fight can turn into a thing, you know.

00:57:33.688 --> 00:57:36.226
I have a feeling they'll work it out.

00:57:52.980 --> 00:57:55.746
A long time ago, churches would

00:57:56.489 --> 00:58:01.335
take in runaways
and people wanted by the government.

00:58:10.230 --> 00:58:12.346
Ui Yeong?

00:59:05.980 --> 00:59:08.186
You'll have to purchase
the ticket for one adult.

00:59:08.186 --> 00:59:09.820
Okay.

00:59:50.396 --> 00:59:51.813
Oh, it's cold.

00:59:51.813 --> 00:59:54.209
[We handle everything for pop-ups,
from space design to day-to-day ops]

00:59:54.209 --> 00:59:57.326
[Styling and exhibition spaces
that match your brand's vibe perfectly]

01:00:05.418 --> 01:00:07.839
Where did you go?
There's mud all over the front door.

01:00:07.839 --> 01:00:11.707
Oh, that... Just let me hang this up real quick
and I'll take care of it.

01:00:11.707 --> 01:00:14.293
And when you stay out overnight,
giving a heads-up beforehand

01:00:14.293 --> 01:00:16.439
is just basic courtesy
to the person you live with.

01:00:16.439 --> 01:00:17.839
It's a scary world out there.

01:00:17.839 --> 01:00:19.118
Oh, I'm sorry.

01:00:19.118 --> 01:00:21.592
I had to rush to Chuncheon out of nowhere

01:00:21.592 --> 01:00:22.764
and my phone went dead.

01:00:22.764 --> 01:00:24.939
I left the office in such a hurry

01:00:24.939 --> 01:00:26.838
that I forgot my charger.

01:00:26.838 --> 01:00:28.565
I'm sorry.

01:00:29.371 --> 01:00:31.276
What's that hoodie?

01:00:31.962 --> 01:00:32.979
This one?

01:00:32.979 --> 01:00:35.902
What about it? It's oversized.

01:00:35.902 --> 01:00:40.035
You don't know everyone's wearing
stuff like this now?

01:00:45.897 --> 01:00:49.019
I met with them and tried my best
to convince them,

01:00:49.019 --> 01:00:50.203
but it didn't work out.

01:00:50.203 --> 01:00:51.803
Did you actually try?

01:00:51.803 --> 01:00:53.788
I don't think that's something
you should say to someone

01:00:53.788 --> 01:00:55.363
who went all the way to Chuncheon
and put in the work.

01:00:55.363 --> 01:00:57.442
You're... right.

01:00:57.442 --> 01:00:59.759
It looks like HOME and us need some time

01:00:59.759 --> 01:01:01.599
to repair the relationship.

01:01:01.599 --> 01:01:04.798
For now, I'll focus on finding a new vendor.

01:01:04.798 --> 01:01:07.850
Everyone will need to work overtime
until we confirm a new vendor.

01:01:07.850 --> 01:01:09.595
Got it.

01:01:11.896 --> 01:01:14.069
Seriously, this is so stressful.

01:01:14.896 --> 01:01:15.998
Sorry.

01:01:15.998 --> 01:01:18.198
It's fine.

01:01:20.313 --> 01:01:22.924
Sae Byeok, it's okay.

01:01:22.924 --> 01:01:25.813
I made a list of new vendors last night.

01:01:25.813 --> 01:01:27.116
I'll send it to you.

01:01:27.116 --> 01:01:28.669
Please check for any plagiarism issues.

01:01:28.669 --> 01:01:29.405
Oh, okay.

01:01:29.405 --> 01:01:31.905
Hyun Min, let's split up
and reach out to the vendors.

01:01:31.905 --> 01:01:33.525
First, let's see
if they can work with our schedule.

01:01:33.525 --> 01:01:36.045
Sure, send me the list
and I'll start calling them from the top.

01:01:36.045 --> 01:01:37.509
Sounds good.

01:01:39.313 --> 01:01:41.984
I love this! Isn't it great?

01:01:41.984 --> 01:01:43.799
I picked it up secondhand
to read over the weekend.

01:01:43.799 --> 01:01:45.265
I heard it's a masterpiece.

01:01:45.265 --> 01:01:47.904
It is. Once you start,
you really can't put it down.

01:01:47.904 --> 01:01:50.563
But you're still on volume one?

01:01:50.563 --> 01:01:52.730
Something else caught my interest,

01:01:52.730 --> 01:01:54.521
so I haven't started it yet.

01:01:54.521 --> 01:01:57.154
What's that?

01:01:57.813 --> 01:02:00.532
[Song Tae Seop]

01:02:04.824 --> 01:02:06.158
Hello?

01:02:06.158 --> 01:02:08.188
It's me.

01:02:08.188 --> 01:02:08.934
Oh, hi.

01:02:08.934 --> 01:02:11.059
What brings you to call at this hour?

01:02:11.059 --> 01:02:12.359
Can I see you now?

01:02:12.359 --> 01:02:14.622
I have something important to tell you.

01:02:14.622 --> 01:02:16.165
I'll come by your office.

01:02:16.165 --> 01:02:18.425
Oh, sure.

01:02:44.043 --> 01:02:46.828
What's so important?

01:02:57.123 --> 01:02:58.666
[I'm here]

01:02:58.666 --> 01:03:01.343
[Take your time]

01:03:05.006 --> 01:03:07.044
Oh, Ui Yeong! You're here.

01:03:07.044 --> 01:03:08.271
Yeah, hi! How have you been?

01:03:08.271 --> 01:03:10.524
- We got a new part-timer, did you know?
- Oh, really?

01:03:10.524 --> 01:03:11.887
I've been training him.

01:03:11.887 --> 01:03:13.371
I see.

01:03:13.371 --> 01:03:14.232
What would you like?

01:03:14.232 --> 01:03:15.932
I'll have a hot latte.

01:03:15.932 --> 01:03:17.352
One hot latte.

01:03:17.352 --> 01:03:19.983
So the last part-timer quit?

01:03:19.983 --> 01:03:22.146
Oh, that one was so unreliable.

01:03:22.146 --> 01:03:23.188
I see.

01:03:23.188 --> 01:03:25.212
I think I picked a good one this time.

01:03:25.212 --> 01:03:27.365
Oh, nice.

01:03:27.365 --> 01:03:29.611
Here he comes.

01:03:29.611 --> 01:03:31.741
She is one of our regulars at the cafe.

01:03:31.741 --> 01:03:33.917
She works at the hotel up there.

01:03:35.662 --> 01:03:37.307
Shin Ji Su.

01:03:37.307 --> 01:03:38.063
What?

01:03:38.063 --> 01:03:39.040
Hi.

01:03:39.040 --> 01:03:40.551
Do you two know each other?

01:03:40.551 --> 01:03:42.514
A little.

01:03:42.514 --> 01:03:43.654
What the...

01:03:43.654 --> 01:03:46.596
What are you doing here now?

01:03:47.271 --> 01:03:49.057
Well...

01:04:21.708 --> 01:04:24.840
I really like him.

01:04:28.600 --> 01:04:30.223
Here you go.

01:04:32.176 --> 01:04:35.016
So how did you end up working here?

01:04:35.016 --> 01:04:37.380
The theater season ended,

01:04:37.380 --> 01:04:40.340
and I got fired from the restaurant
for walking out.

01:04:40.340 --> 01:04:41.661
I still need to eat, so here I am.

01:04:41.661 --> 01:04:44.563
Oh, the play you invited me to last time,

01:04:44.563 --> 01:04:46.841
something urgent came up
and I couldn't make it.

01:04:46.841 --> 01:04:47.600
Sorry.

01:04:47.600 --> 01:04:48.527
Yeah.

01:04:48.527 --> 01:04:51.423
I kept wondering if you'd show up,
even if it was late,

01:04:51.423 --> 01:04:53.117
but you never did.

01:04:53.117 --> 01:04:56.082
Oh, you were waiting?

01:04:57.063 --> 01:04:58.638
I'm just kidding.

01:04:58.638 --> 01:05:01.855
You can't really see the audience
from the stage anyway.

01:05:01.855 --> 01:05:04.978
Acting's my job, so I'll keep doing shows.

01:05:04.978 --> 01:05:05.918
Come next time.

01:05:05.918 --> 01:05:07.139
I'll get you a ticket again.

01:05:07.139 --> 01:05:08.319
Okay, sure.

01:05:08.319 --> 01:05:09.971
Thanks.

01:05:11.011 --> 01:05:12.019
Then buy me a meal.

01:05:12.019 --> 01:05:14.019
One for being sorry, one for being grateful.

01:05:14.019 --> 01:05:16.269
That's two meals.

01:05:18.013 --> 01:05:19.271
Hey,

01:05:19.271 --> 01:05:22.838
but weren't you the one
who owed me an apology first?

01:05:22.838 --> 01:05:24.478
Yeah.

01:05:24.478 --> 01:05:27.355
But you're not taking that back.

01:05:27.355 --> 01:05:30.655
You always find a way
to get a free meal from me.

01:05:30.655 --> 01:05:32.011
How about tomorrow evening?

01:05:32.011 --> 01:05:34.480
I'm working the closing shift tonight.

01:05:34.480 --> 01:05:35.647
Tomorrow...

01:05:35.647 --> 01:05:37.339
Ui Yeong.

01:05:38.063 --> 01:05:40.502
Tae Seop. You're here?

01:05:44.624 --> 01:05:45.892
He can't tell who it is, right?

01:05:45.892 --> 01:05:48.969
We meet again, cousin.

01:05:52.104 --> 01:05:55.101
Why does this feel so familiar?

01:05:55.101 --> 01:05:58.770
Are we just supposed
to walk out that door together now?

01:05:59.772 --> 01:06:02.023
That's not going to happen.

01:06:14.480 --> 01:06:16.730
Yesterday.

01:06:16.730 --> 01:06:18.601
Yesterday?

01:06:18.601 --> 01:06:20.834
We kissed.

01:06:21.577 --> 01:06:22.624
What?

01:06:22.624 --> 01:06:24.772
I was so jittery about seeing you again

01:06:24.772 --> 01:06:27.132
that sleep completely escaped me.

01:06:29.688 --> 01:06:31.636
Did you manage to get any rest?

01:06:53.776 --> 01:06:56.946
[Our timing kept missing]

01:06:56.946 --> 01:07:00.032
[You look like a baked sweet potato]

01:07:00.032 --> 01:07:03.140
[You're still on my mind]

01:07:06.747 --> 01:07:10.467
[The left hand just backs you up]

01:07:13.712 --> 01:07:16.726
[If that's a sin, I'll make up for it one day]

01:07:24.063 --> 01:07:25.815
You want to...

01:07:26.517 --> 01:07:28.001
do what together?

01:07:28.001 --> 01:07:29.688
Ki...

01:07:29.688 --> 01:07:33.194
I should have just finished what I started.

01:07:33.194 --> 01:07:35.521
So are you two dating?

01:07:35.521 --> 01:07:37.782
You're not twenty.
You're giving away your heart over one kiss?

01:07:37.782 --> 01:07:40.561
I really like you, Seung Jun.

01:07:41.282 --> 01:07:43.121
Calm down and use your words.

01:07:43.121 --> 01:07:44.688
We came up with ideas today.

01:07:44.688 --> 01:07:46.495
After work...

01:07:46.495 --> 01:07:48.305
It feels so refreshing.

01:07:48.305 --> 01:07:51.370
You're right there within reach,

01:07:51.370 --> 01:07:55.512
but I can't quite hold on to you,
and it's driving me crazy.

01:07:56.313 --> 01:07:59.349
Did I really sleep with him?